### Scope IN
1) **At-rest protection** (checkpoint + workflow persistence) with rollback:\n
   - Implement `SecurePostgresSaver` (AES-256-GCM) or equivalent wrapper that encrypts checkpoint payloads.\n
   - Encryption scope MUST include both:\n
     - `checkpoint_blobs` (payload blobs)\n
     - `checkpoint_writes` (channel values)\n
   - Key management v1:\n
     - `CHECKPOINT_ENCRYPTION_KEY` env var\n
     - no default value\n
     - format validation (32 bytes / 256-bit)\n
     - **fail start** in production exposure mode if key missing/invalid\n
2) **Crypto migration plan**:\n
   - Backfill/re-encrypt existing plaintext rows.\n
   - Include rollback strategy (restore DB backup; disable encryption wrapper only if data loss risk is controlled).\n
3) **No-raw-content enforcement** as gates (not prose):\n
   - Deterministic canary injection.\n
   - Deterministic scans across:\n
     - docker logs\n
     - Langfuse trace exports\n
     - DB sample rows from relevant tables\n
   - Explicit exclusions list (IDs allowed; raw user/doc text forbidden).\n
   - Fail-closed behavior for production exposure.\n
4) **Langfuse self-hosted** spec + verification:\n
   - Provide compose or infra method to run Langfuse at :3001.\n
   - Gate must verify:\n
     - `GET http://localhost:3001/api/public/health` returns 2xx\n
     - At least one trace is created for a defined workflow\n
     - No raw content appears in the trace export\n
5) **Resilience contract** for external services (tool gateway):\n
   - Define and implement timeouts/retries/backoff/circuit breakers for Deal API, RAG REST, MCP.\n
   - Record config snapshot as an artifact.\n
 
